South African Central Bank’s Marcus Comments on Inflation

-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 
2011-03-24T13:07:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/south-african-central-bank-s-marcus-comments-on-inflation.html
South African Reserve Bank
Governor Gill Marcus made the following comments on inflation
after a meeting of the bank’s monetary policy committee in
 Pretoria  today.  “The risk to inflation has increased to the upside.  “Inflation is still expected to remain within the target
range over the entire forecast period.  “Inflation is now expected to average 4.7 percent in 2011
and 5.7 percent in 2012.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mike Cohen in Cape Town at 
 mcohen21@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Barden at   barden@bloomberg.net  